1
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:37,954
{\an8}UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

2
00:00:38,997 --> 00:00:40,957
{\an8}I'll get right to the point.

3
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:43,626
{\an8}This is what Uncle Myeong-hwi compiled
to blow the whistle with…

4
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:45,545
{\an8}It's the slush fund ledger.

5
00:00:45,628 --> 00:00:47,881
{\an8}The FSS does not want to investigate,

6
00:00:47,964 --> 00:00:50,633
{\an8}and Hanmin is being targeted
by both internal and external forces.

7
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:52,260
{\an8}You mean DK Ventures and President Shin?

8
00:00:52,343 --> 00:00:53,470
{\an8}We figured out as much.

9
00:00:53,553 --> 00:00:56,222
{\an8}Our ultimate goal is to steal
the slush fund, buy up the stock,

10
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:58,808
{\an8}and become the major shareholder
to protect the company.

11
00:01:00,185 --> 00:01:01,352
{\an8}Hold on.

12
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:05,231
{\an8}The company would fall right into your lap
even if you did nothing, Big Al.

13
00:01:05,315 --> 00:01:06,733
{\an8}Why take such a big gamble?

14
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:08,693
{\an8}How can we know you're serious?

15
00:01:08,777 --> 00:01:11,529
{\an8}Let's say I do become Hanmin's president,
just as my father wishes.

16
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:13,031
Then what?

17
00:01:13,114 --> 00:01:14,532
What if I get replaced
like Uncle Myeong-hwi did?

18
00:01:14,616 --> 00:01:16,201
That's not the ending I want for myself.

19
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:19,871
All right, we've decided to
board the same boat,

20
00:01:19,954 --> 00:01:22,415
so even if we end up hating each other
enough to throw someone overboard,

21
00:01:22,499 --> 00:01:25,293
we'll still work together
until we reach our destination.

22
00:01:25,376 --> 00:01:26,211
Okay?

23
00:01:27,587 --> 00:01:28,963
Division Manager Oh.

24
00:01:29,047 --> 00:01:30,673
I'll be watching you.

25
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:31,591
So what?

26
00:01:33,259 --> 00:01:34,302
Okay.

27
00:01:35,678 --> 00:01:36,596
Let's get back to it.

28
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:40,350
Our first target is
the domestic slush funds.

29
00:01:40,433 --> 00:01:41,392
Who manages them?

30
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:47,190
DOMESTIC SLUSH FUNDS

31
00:01:47,273 --> 00:01:49,442
{\an8}"Managed by Executive Director
Oh Deok-gyu"?

32
00:01:50,527 --> 00:01:51,361
My dad?

33
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:00,745
Good day, sir.

34
00:02:03,581 --> 00:02:04,541
I'll leave you to it.

35
00:02:04,624 --> 00:02:05,959
- All right.
- Yes.

36
00:02:13,424 --> 00:02:15,844
Now that the election has wrapped up,

37
00:02:16,636 --> 00:02:20,014
I've been thinking it's about time
to deliver the interest payments.

38
00:02:20,723 --> 00:02:22,475
It's our annual event, after all.

39
00:02:22,559 --> 00:02:24,435
Executive Director Oh,

40
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:26,729
I appreciate your hard work.

41
00:02:27,605 --> 00:02:28,481
Not at all, sir.

42
00:02:29,357 --> 00:02:30,984
Just keep it up for one last year.

43
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:36,114
By one last year, do you mean…

44
00:02:36,698 --> 00:02:37,740
<i>Could it be?</i>

45
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:40,827
<i>Is he finally rolling out</i>
<i>a new succession plan?</i>

46
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:44,706
Tasks like these
are better suited for young people.

47
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:47,917
Or I can have Ms. Song take on the task.

48
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:51,546
Wait, sir.

49
00:02:52,046 --> 00:02:53,006
Ms. Song isn't fit for this.

50
00:02:53,882 --> 00:02:56,217
We must treat our VIP clients
with full honors,

51
00:02:56,301 --> 00:02:58,970
and they would be insulted
if a chief of staff showed up.

52
00:02:59,053 --> 00:03:01,347
Ms. Song isn't suited to their level.

53
00:03:01,431 --> 00:03:02,348
Is that so?

54
00:03:03,474 --> 00:03:05,184
Then how about Shin Jung-woo?

55
00:03:05,268 --> 00:03:06,352
He's a president.

56
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:08,897
You would already entrust
the young president

57
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:10,982
with a task of such paramount importance?

58
00:03:11,065 --> 00:03:14,027
You should've done a better job then.

59
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:19,032
Our failure to secure that public funding
was partly your fault too.

60
00:03:19,115 --> 00:03:22,911
You clearly failed
to properly manage our VIP clients.

61
00:03:22,994 --> 00:03:24,996
Even the total balance is lower this year!

62
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:26,664
Father-in-law… I mean, sir.

63
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:29,042
I promise I will do better.

64
00:03:39,302 --> 00:03:41,429
<i>That's not a place for Ms. Song.</i>

65
00:03:42,013 --> 00:03:43,514
<i>Not for Shin Jung-woo either.</i>

66
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:47,060
<i>You two will be bowing down to me.</i>

67
00:03:47,852 --> 00:03:49,354
<i>I will make sure of it,</i>

68
00:03:49,938 --> 00:03:50,813
<i>no matter what.</i>

69
00:03:56,736 --> 00:04:00,907
You and I share
so many similarities, don't we?

70
00:04:00,990 --> 00:04:02,825
We do?

71
00:04:03,576 --> 00:04:05,495
Live-in son-in-laws.

72
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:09,874
We're family chosen by the chairman.

73
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:13,086
The world is
so full of surprises, isn't it?

74
00:04:13,169 --> 00:04:15,255
We were strangers just three months ago,

75
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:17,715
but in the new year,
we'll be brothers-in-law.

76
00:04:19,550 --> 00:04:22,303
I'd like to ask you to briefly state
the purpose of your visit.

77
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:25,265
As you can see,
I have a lot on my plate right now.

78
00:04:27,141 --> 00:04:28,851
I had an important chat

79
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:31,479
with the chairman just a while ago.

80
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:32,814
Gosh.

81
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:37,026
It seems like he believes
you share some of the blame

82
00:04:37,110 --> 00:04:39,320
for failing to secure that public funding.

83
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,781
I'm sure he was very disappointed.

84
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:45,910
But I still made sure to safeguard you.

85
00:04:47,578 --> 00:04:51,082
Despite how things may look,
the chairman has great faith in me.

86
00:04:51,165 --> 00:04:53,001
He even entrusted me with a special task,

87
00:04:53,084 --> 00:04:55,878
but I recommended you
as my successor earlier

88
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,088
for that very position.

89
00:04:57,839 --> 00:04:59,424
And what exactly is this task?

90
00:05:01,718 --> 00:05:03,219
It's still confidential,
so I can't say more.

91
00:05:07,515 --> 00:05:09,225
If the chairman summons you,

92
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:11,227
be sure to reach out to me first.

93
00:05:12,186 --> 00:05:14,647
Then I'll gladly turn over
the task to you.

94
00:05:15,398 --> 00:05:16,524
All right?

95
00:05:33,082 --> 00:05:34,917
Hello, I'm calling from Admin.

96
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:36,753
Are you all set?

97
00:05:36,836 --> 00:05:38,004
Is my dad already on his way?

98
00:05:38,963 --> 00:05:40,256
I haven't found it yet.

99
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,717
- The white pot.
- The white pot?

100
00:05:47,055 --> 00:05:47,930
Okay.

101
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:06,199
Dad, you seem to be in a good mood.

102
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:09,744
I heard you were meeting with the chairman
when I called earlier.

103
00:06:09,827 --> 00:06:10,703
Did something happen?

104
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:11,746
Is your dad…

105
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:16,542
someone who only goes to see the chairman
when something happens?

106
00:06:17,543 --> 00:06:19,670
You keep so many secrets from me.

107
00:06:21,047 --> 00:06:23,091
Especially when it comes to
anything about the chairman.

108
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:25,802
My son.

109
00:06:27,845 --> 00:06:28,679
Such a handsome guy.

110
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:31,516
Albert, Oh Deok-gyu's boy.

111
00:06:33,601 --> 00:06:34,894
Where should I begin

112
00:06:34,977 --> 00:06:39,065
in sharing my wisdom with you, son?

113
00:06:42,693 --> 00:06:44,403
Under the chairman's orders,

114
00:06:45,154 --> 00:06:47,281
I've been running a small operation.

115
00:06:48,032 --> 00:06:50,952
Then out of the blue,
he wants someone else to take over.

116
00:06:51,035 --> 00:06:52,120
What sort of operation?

117
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:59,669
Delivering the interest payments
of politicians' slush funds.

118
00:07:00,461 --> 00:07:01,295
Bang.

119
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:05,800
Why would you bother?

120
00:07:06,384 --> 00:07:07,593
Just hand it all over.

121
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:08,928
It's nice not having to work.

122
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:11,430
But wait.

123
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:13,141
I thought you knew nothing
about the slush fund.

124
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:14,934
Yeah.

125
00:07:15,017 --> 00:07:17,019
You said only Grandpa
and Ms. Song knew about it.

126
00:07:23,025 --> 00:07:26,154
This is why I'm always a step behind
Auntie Nora and President Shin.

127
00:07:27,196 --> 00:07:28,281
You feel it too, right?

128
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:31,033
<i>Tasks like these</i>

129
00:07:31,117 --> 00:07:33,161
are better suited for young people.

130
00:07:34,495 --> 00:07:35,413
Right?

131
00:07:35,872 --> 00:07:37,415
I can't hand this over to President Shin.

132
00:07:37,498 --> 00:07:38,583
I could, if it were you.

133
00:07:40,418 --> 00:07:41,252
All right.

134
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:45,465
You see, all politicians need funds.

135
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:01,022
Did you meet with your father?

136
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:06,027
It turns out my dad secretly went around
making deals with politicians every year.

137
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:09,947
He offers to manage funds
they want kept hidden,

138
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:11,657
with annual interest payouts.

139
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:12,867
So it's a political slush fund.

140
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:14,994
Just forget about it.

141
00:08:15,077 --> 00:08:15,953
We can't steal that money.

142
00:08:16,954 --> 00:08:19,373
You're saying
the slush funds will be moved again

143
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:20,583
if we miss this chance, right?

144
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:21,709
Right.

145
00:08:21,792 --> 00:08:24,837
It's a one-year contract, so there are
withdrawals and new clients every year.

146
00:08:25,421 --> 00:08:26,839
And according to my dad,

147
00:08:26,923 --> 00:08:29,175
the chairman wishes to appoint
a new manager.

148
00:08:29,258 --> 00:08:30,510
Listen to me.

149
00:08:30,593 --> 00:08:32,386
We can't go after a political slush fund.

150
00:08:33,554 --> 00:08:34,514
Damn it.

151
00:08:35,014 --> 00:08:37,683
We'll have to make
Executive Director Oh invite us in.

152
00:08:38,392 --> 00:08:39,435
It won't be easy.

153
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:42,355
He's just as vigilant as the chairman,

154
00:08:42,438 --> 00:08:44,607
and he only associates
with vetted individuals.

155
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:46,817
Schooling, money, and social influence.

156
00:08:47,652 --> 00:08:49,195
Those kinds of power
matter very much to him.

157
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:53,282
{\an8}OH DEOK-GYU 9%

158
00:08:53,366 --> 00:08:54,325
Hello, Assemblyman.

159
00:08:54,408 --> 00:08:55,493
I hope all is well.

160
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:57,912
Thank you for your service
to this country.

161
00:08:59,997 --> 00:09:01,165
Take care, sir.

162
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,001
When's the next one?

163
00:09:04,085 --> 00:09:05,920
- In 30 minutes, sir.
- Make sure we're ready.

164
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:24,355
A HISTORY OF FINANCIAL CRIMES
WRITTEN BY YUN JAE-BEOM

165
00:09:24,438 --> 00:09:26,482
"A History of Financial Crimes"?

166
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:29,485
It's training material
from the FSS new hire training.

167
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:32,280
It's a compilation of case studies
on various financial crimes

168
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:35,825
that were prevalent in Korea
from Liberation through the late '80s.

169
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:39,870
Have you heard of the old banknote scam?

170
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:44,834
<i>Five suspects,</i>
<i>including a man surnamed Kim,</i>

171
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:47,628
<i>have been indicted while in custody</i>
<i>for a scam involving old banknotes.</i>

172
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:49,088
<i>The group approached victims,</i>

173
00:09:49,171 --> 00:09:52,592
<i>claiming to manage</i>
<i>tens of trillions of won in slush funds</i>

174
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:54,885
<i>a former administration siphoned</i>
<i>from the national mint.</i>

175
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:57,722
<i>They lured victims</i>
<i>by proposing to exchange</i>

176
00:09:57,805 --> 00:10:00,808
<i>6 billion won in old banknotes</i>
<i>for 4.2 billion in 10,000-won notes,</i>

177
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:04,186
<i>promising the remaining 30% as commission.</i>

178
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,939
They hooked them
by promising a huge commission

179
00:10:07,023 --> 00:10:09,150
just for exchanging old bills
for new ones?

180
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:11,068
But we don't have any old bills.

181
00:10:11,152 --> 00:10:12,737
We'll pretend to,
which is why it's a fraud.

182
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:15,740
It's a con by reverse-engineering
existing criminal schemes.

183
00:10:15,823 --> 00:10:16,991
You got it, Mr. Lee.

184
00:10:17,992 --> 00:10:20,620
But wouldn't we still need
some old bills to use as bait?

185
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:22,204
I've already acquired some.

186
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:25,124
I asked when we went to that office
near the Bank of Korea.

187
00:10:34,675 --> 00:10:37,553
Can you source about 500 million won
in old 10,000-won bills?

188
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:38,596
What?

189
00:10:49,065 --> 00:10:49,899
Wow.

190
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:53,694
First phase of the operation,

191
00:10:53,778 --> 00:10:56,197
we start a rumor about old banknotes.

192
00:10:57,198 --> 00:10:59,450
This rumor must start quietly spreading

193
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:01,994
from the Myeongdong markets to Yeouido.

194
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:05,873
But Yeouido Pirates,
the perfect rumor mill, was shut down.

195
00:11:05,956 --> 00:11:08,793
If it resurfaces now,
it'll only arouse suspicion.

196
00:11:08,876 --> 00:11:10,753
So let's utilize other speakers.

197
00:11:23,015 --> 00:11:25,309
EPISODE 12: MONEY NEVER SLEEPS

198
00:11:27,144 --> 00:11:30,898
{\an8}DIRECTOR YUN JAE-BEOM

199
00:11:30,981 --> 00:11:32,400
She hands in her resignation,

200
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,653
and now she's with Hanmin, inside and out.

201
00:11:36,987 --> 00:11:37,947
Damn it.

202
00:11:40,074 --> 00:11:41,450
Jeez.

203
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:46,997
You've reached--

204
00:11:47,081 --> 00:11:49,083
<i>- Still at the office, Director Yun?</i>
- Hong!

205
00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:51,043
<i>Hey!</i>

206
00:11:51,127 --> 00:11:52,086
Hold on.

207
00:11:53,671 --> 00:11:55,965
Speak of the devil, huh?

208
00:11:57,758 --> 00:12:00,469
Wait, are you watching me from somewhere?

209
00:12:00,553 --> 00:12:04,014
You answered in that tone you use
when you're at work.

210
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:07,309
I called thinking you might be interested
in a progress report.

211
00:12:07,393 --> 00:12:08,561
And I have a favor to ask.

212
00:12:08,644 --> 00:12:10,479
You think I have time to waste like that?

213
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:12,773
Why would I care
what you people are up to?

214
00:12:12,857 --> 00:12:13,941
My goodness.

215
00:12:14,483 --> 00:12:16,402
Forget it then. Bye.

216
00:12:16,485 --> 00:12:18,028
Wait, no. Hey!

217
00:12:19,697 --> 00:12:22,116
You need to hear me out to the end.

218
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:25,828
Before I'm your boss,
I'm your mentor in life.

219
00:12:25,911 --> 00:12:27,997
A mentor could offer some aid, right?

220
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:31,292
So what is it?

221
00:12:43,846 --> 00:12:46,056
Sir, what did you want to
speak to me about?

222
00:12:48,642 --> 00:12:49,518
The thing is…

223
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:50,686
Yes?

224
00:12:54,482 --> 00:12:55,524
No, never mind.

225
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:00,571
Since when did we have secrets between us?

226
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:02,740
Please don't hesitate to tell me.

227
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:05,075
You know I can keep a secret.

228
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:09,997
I need a rumor to spread like wildfire,

229
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:13,042
and I was hoping to use
Nam Dong-gi as the loudspeaker.

230
00:13:20,925 --> 00:13:23,302
- You cannot tell anyone else.
- Yes, sir.

231
00:13:23,385 --> 00:13:26,889
I went through back channels
to pry this intel out of an informant.

232
00:13:26,972 --> 00:13:28,140
Okay.

233
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:32,311
They've already swept through
the Myeongdong markets.

234
00:13:32,394 --> 00:13:33,229
What did?

235
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:35,272
Exactly.

236
00:13:35,356 --> 00:13:37,399
That's precisely why I'm only telling you.

237
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:39,318
This must stay between us.

238
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:41,570
Of course. I won't tell a soul.

239
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:52,081
I swear I won't tell anyone,
even with a knife to my throat.

240
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:56,126
Not a word.

241
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:14,979
Let me get this straight.

242
00:14:15,062 --> 00:14:16,146
So,

243
00:14:16,814 --> 00:14:21,193
they're exchanging banknotes
to launder political funds?

244
00:14:22,152 --> 00:14:25,364
Sir, you summed it up perfectly.

245
00:14:25,447 --> 00:14:26,824
This is clearly top-tier intel.

246
00:14:26,907 --> 00:14:28,617
It sounds like a scam.

247
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:29,994
They could just use the cash,

248
00:14:30,077 --> 00:14:32,496
so why would they bother
paying a 30% commission?

249
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:34,707
They're just laundering it.

250
00:14:34,790 --> 00:14:37,960
Old bills draw attention from the start,
just by how they look.

251
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:40,379
That commission is
just a drop in the bucket for them.

252
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:44,842
Word is they've already swept through
the Myeongdong markets once.

253
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:47,344
Then again,

254
00:14:48,345 --> 00:14:52,349
Myeongdong and Yeouido
are overflowing with easy money.

255
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:55,978
Don't push it.

256
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:07,907
Time for some music.

257
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:12,286
Let me try an approach shot
while listening to music.

258
00:15:13,203 --> 00:15:14,705
You need a clean spin for…

259
00:15:16,665 --> 00:15:19,877
Word is they've already swept through
the Myeongdong markets once.

260
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:23,047
I hear they call you directly
as if you've been personally selected.

261
00:15:25,257 --> 00:15:27,051
Damn fool.

262
00:15:27,134 --> 00:15:29,720
Nothing is free in this world.

263
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:33,307
Focus.

264
00:15:39,355 --> 00:15:40,648
Yes, hello?

265
00:15:41,273 --> 00:15:42,524
<i>Executive Director Oh Deok-gyu.</i>

266
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:45,194
Yes, that's me. Who might you be?

267
00:15:45,277 --> 00:15:47,112
<i>I'd like to make you an offer.</i>

268
00:15:47,905 --> 00:15:50,074
<i>I'm in need of some fresh,</i>
<i>crisp 10,000-won bills.</i>

269
00:15:52,618 --> 00:15:54,078
You're the 30% commission guy.

270
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:56,121
<i>If you can meet the timeframe,</i>

271
00:15:56,205 --> 00:15:58,040
<i>I can even offer up to 50%.</i>

272
00:15:58,123 --> 00:15:59,625
Right. Sure.

273
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:01,543
Who the hell are you?

274
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,796
How dare you try to scam me?

275
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:05,130
Do you know who I am, punk?

276
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:08,550
How are you going to gain
Executive Director Oh's trust?

277
00:16:09,551 --> 00:16:11,637
I get that you'll spread a rumor
that seems convincing,

278
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:14,390
and that you'll use
Mr. Lee's voice-altering program.

279
00:16:14,473 --> 00:16:15,557
But still,

280
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:17,309
you won't be able to
make the deal in person.

281
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:20,020
My dad is a greedy man,

282
00:16:20,646 --> 00:16:21,563
and he's just as wary.

283
00:16:24,149 --> 00:16:25,526
We have this.

284
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,280
<i>- Yehppee!</i>
- The names of politicians

285
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:32,741
who have entrusted Hanmin
with their slush funds,

286
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:34,368
as well as their account balances.

287
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:37,454
<i>Song Hui-seop, five billion won.</i>

288
00:16:37,538 --> 00:16:39,081
<i>Lee Yong-ja, 1.2 billion won.</i>

289
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:41,792
<i>Lee Cheong-ju, 1.5 billion won.</i>

290
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:45,087
Wait, how do you know about that?

291
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:46,797
<i>I'm only reaching out to you</i>

292
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:49,049
<i>because I'm on solid terms of trust</i>
<i>with them.</i>

293
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:50,634
<i>Even this past Tuesday,</i>

294
00:16:50,718 --> 00:16:53,137
<i>you worked late into the night</i>
<i>running your operation.</i>

295
00:16:53,762 --> 00:16:57,057
May I ask for your name?

296
00:16:57,141 --> 00:16:59,143
<i>I'll call you again</i>
<i>at the same time in two days.</i>

297
00:16:59,226 --> 00:17:00,310
Wait.

298
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:08,235
What the hell?

299
00:17:19,496 --> 00:17:20,330
Do you think he'll buy it?

300
00:17:21,999 --> 00:17:23,959
He'll probably try to
verify the facts once more.

301
00:17:24,752 --> 00:17:26,962
But I bet he already has an answer
he wants to hear.

302
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:37,222
Why would I suddenly have a meal
with Director Yun Jae-beom?

303
00:17:37,306 --> 00:17:38,307
Well,

304
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:40,142
I suggested we get together
for a casual meal

305
00:17:40,225 --> 00:17:42,186
to celebrate the year's end
and the new year.

306
00:17:42,269 --> 00:17:44,063
A get-together
to verify some facts, if you will.

307
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:46,857
Unnecessary meetings
can easily lead to mistakes.

308
00:17:47,399 --> 00:17:50,944
What if the FSS was still determined
to pursue the slush fund investigation?

309
00:17:51,028 --> 00:17:52,738
Who? Them?

310
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:57,242
That ship sailed ages ago,
and no idiot would cling to that case.

311
00:17:57,326 --> 00:18:01,288
And with the consolidation of securities,
banking, and insurance regulators,

312
00:18:01,371 --> 00:18:03,457
they're too busy saving their own skin.

313
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:05,793
Saving their own skin…

314
00:18:05,876 --> 00:18:09,421
<i>The problem is, there's an idiot</i>
<i>who refuses to do just that.</i>

315
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:11,048
So?

316
00:18:11,131 --> 00:18:11,965
Are you saying

317
00:18:12,549 --> 00:18:15,344
you're not joining me for the meal?

318
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:17,763
No, I'll join.

319
00:18:24,978 --> 00:18:27,606
The other day, Mr. Nam Dong-gi

320
00:18:27,689 --> 00:18:29,817
shared something very interesting with me.

321
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:31,443
Something about old banknotes,

322
00:18:31,527 --> 00:18:33,153
and exchanging them and such.

323
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:34,446
My goodness.

324
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:35,572
Pardon?

325
00:18:37,324 --> 00:18:39,201
That damn punk.

326
00:18:39,701 --> 00:18:43,497
That's a top-secret matter
we're handling jointly and off the record.

327
00:18:43,580 --> 00:18:46,625
Did he already spill
all the details to you?

328
00:18:47,126 --> 00:18:51,171
That damn loudmouth can't keep
his mouth shut to save his life.

329
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:55,884
Am I the only one in the dark about this?

330
00:18:58,345 --> 00:19:01,223
Oh, please allow me to explain.

331
00:19:02,015 --> 00:19:03,350
I was actually planning

332
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:06,228
to reach out to Hanmin
to discuss this matter.

333
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:10,816
I mean, private currency exchanges
with premium charges?

334
00:19:10,899 --> 00:19:12,401
If the money's source was legitimate,

335
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:15,821
nobody in their right mind
would go through all that trouble.

336
00:19:15,904 --> 00:19:18,323
We can't allow
such disruptions in our market.

337
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:20,951
They could reach out
to the financial or securities sector,

338
00:19:21,034 --> 00:19:22,411
where capital is easily mobilized.

339
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:25,164
If, by chance,
you ever receive such an offer,

340
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:27,624
please be sure to report it to us.

341
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:29,710
Yes, I will gladly do my part.

342
00:19:29,793 --> 00:19:30,669
Thank you.

343
00:19:32,546 --> 00:19:34,923
Have you already received such a call,
by any chance?

344
00:19:36,717 --> 00:19:37,718
What?

345
00:19:39,219 --> 00:19:40,554
It looks like you have.

346
00:19:44,099 --> 00:19:44,933
Nope.

347
00:19:46,476 --> 00:19:47,311
Never.

348
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:49,897
What do you take me for?

349
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:56,486
What a fun world we live in.

350
00:20:18,383 --> 00:20:21,094
Hello, you've reached Oh Deok-gyu.

351
00:20:21,178 --> 00:20:23,013
<i>Have you given it some thought?</i>

352
00:20:23,096 --> 00:20:25,891
Yes, I did give it some thought,

353
00:20:25,974 --> 00:20:30,270
but you should at least tell me
your name and where your office is…

354
00:20:30,354 --> 00:20:32,105
<i>If I said it's a house</i>
<i>with a blue-tiled roof,</i>

355
00:20:32,189 --> 00:20:33,357
<i>would that be enough?</i>

356
00:20:38,195 --> 00:20:40,280
Well, for the first deal,

357
00:20:40,364 --> 00:20:43,909
I was hoping I could suggest the amount.

358
00:20:44,618 --> 00:20:45,535
What do you say?

359
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:56,380
- Careful.
- Be careful right here.

360
00:20:59,549 --> 00:21:01,969
It's 1.5 billion with the 50% commission.
You double-checked, right?

361
00:21:02,552 --> 00:21:03,428
Of course.

362
00:21:03,512 --> 00:21:05,055
We're not giving him a single cent more.

363
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:08,850
They were so confused when I asked
to exchange new bills for old ones.

364
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:17,192
We'll drop off the old banknotes
at the meeting spot,

365
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:19,945
and then take the new bills
Executive Director Oh leaves behind.

366
00:21:20,904 --> 00:21:22,322
I hope he doesn't just steal it.

367
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:25,075
What if he won't agree
to another deal after this?

368
00:21:25,158 --> 00:21:27,369
He'll change his mind
once he sees the money.

369
00:21:47,597 --> 00:21:48,598
"5879."

370
00:21:48,682 --> 00:21:50,142
"5879." Okay.

371
00:22:09,745 --> 00:22:10,704
Please let it be real.

372
00:22:11,413 --> 00:22:12,914
Come on, let it be real.

373
00:22:24,926 --> 00:22:25,761
Yes!

374
00:22:43,361 --> 00:22:46,073
LUCKY APPLES

375
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:05,217
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

376
00:23:09,221 --> 00:23:10,597
DO NOT TOUCH

377
00:23:31,535 --> 00:23:32,577
I can't believe it worked.

378
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:35,330
That was the easiest 500 million won.

379
00:23:36,039 --> 00:23:37,082
Nice!

380
00:23:37,666 --> 00:23:40,919
Long live Korea!

381
00:23:41,002 --> 00:23:43,797
Way to go, Oh!

382
00:23:45,423 --> 00:23:46,258
Come in.

383
00:23:51,638 --> 00:23:53,682
A courier just dropped this off for you,

384
00:23:53,765 --> 00:23:55,392
and the sender was listed as "K."

385
00:23:55,475 --> 00:23:56,351
"K"?

386
00:23:57,644 --> 00:23:58,478
Thanks.

387
00:23:59,312 --> 00:24:00,147
You may leave.

388
00:24:02,732 --> 00:24:03,608
Good work.

389
00:24:04,484 --> 00:24:07,070
You can wrap up for the day
if there's nothing urgent.

390
00:24:09,197 --> 00:24:10,157
Thank you, sir.

391
00:24:28,842 --> 00:24:29,926
<i>I'm glad the deal went smoothly.</i>

392
00:24:30,010 --> 00:24:31,428
<i>How about ten billion won next time?</i>

393
00:24:31,511 --> 00:24:32,345
Ten billion?

394
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:34,598
<i>I'll be in touch soon.</i>

395
00:24:35,265 --> 00:24:36,183
<i>From K.</i>

396
00:24:36,266 --> 00:24:38,810
The only place that could come up
with an amount like this

397
00:24:38,894 --> 00:24:40,687
would be a shell company.

398
00:24:41,688 --> 00:24:42,647
Wait a minute.

399
00:24:43,273 --> 00:24:44,983
The commission is 50%…

400
00:24:46,484 --> 00:24:47,402
so that's five billion won.

401
00:24:52,991 --> 00:24:54,075
Five billion won…

402
00:24:56,494 --> 00:24:57,829
just there for the taking.

403
00:24:58,705 --> 00:25:00,081
Five billion won.

404
00:25:00,165 --> 00:25:02,542
<i>Jingukjeong Liquor,</i>
<i>the domestic industry leader,</i>

405
00:25:02,626 --> 00:25:06,463
<i>was placed in initial default</i>
<i>after failing to settle a promissory note.</i>

406
00:25:07,047 --> 00:25:09,382
<i>With the foreign exchange crisis</i>
<i>destabilizing the market,</i>

407
00:25:09,466 --> 00:25:13,303
<i>anxiety continues to grow</i>
<i>as physical distribution companies falter.</i>

408
00:25:14,179 --> 00:25:17,849
<i>Jingukjeong Liquor operates</i>
<i>over 1,200 dealerships nationwide…</i>

409
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:21,519
We'll wire the rent money over
by the end of the day.

410
00:25:22,854 --> 00:25:24,147
Yes, all right.

411
00:25:24,731 --> 00:25:26,107
Take care now.

412
00:25:31,821 --> 00:25:34,074
How are we going to
find that money for rent?

413
00:25:36,326 --> 00:25:37,661
Where are you going?

414
00:25:38,578 --> 00:25:39,788
Well…

415
00:25:39,871 --> 00:25:42,374
I'm just going across the street
to Jemulpo Liquor Wholesale

416
00:25:42,457 --> 00:25:45,001
to collect the unpaid bill
for their group dinner last week.

417
00:25:45,085 --> 00:25:46,336
I'll have them clear that tab.

418
00:25:46,419 --> 00:25:47,921
That's not all.

419
00:25:48,004 --> 00:25:50,924
They're also a month behind
on their staff employees' lunch payments.

420
00:25:51,007 --> 00:25:52,509
Who cares if the owner is an alum?

421
00:25:52,592 --> 00:25:54,177
Who cares if you're like brothers?

422
00:25:54,761 --> 00:25:57,180
You'd better clear that tab today
for a month's worth of lunches

423
00:25:57,264 --> 00:25:58,765
and last week's group dinner.

424
00:25:58,848 --> 00:26:00,267
How could I collect all--

425
00:26:00,350 --> 00:26:03,979
Don't even think about coming home
until that tab is completely cleared.

426
00:26:04,062 --> 00:26:06,439
Also, on your way and back,

427
00:26:06,523 --> 00:26:07,649
pass these out.

428
00:26:07,732 --> 00:26:09,776
I even passed these out
at the pool hall last week.

429
00:26:09,859 --> 00:26:11,444
Where else am I supposed to pass them out?

430
00:26:11,528 --> 00:26:12,570
Go.

431
00:26:12,654 --> 00:26:13,822
What's gotten into you?

432
00:26:16,366 --> 00:26:17,534
Darn it.

433
00:26:18,743 --> 00:26:20,787
You're constantly threatening
to kick me out--

434
00:26:20,870 --> 00:26:22,080
- You got this!
- You got this.

435
00:26:23,999 --> 00:26:25,417
"Grandpa, you got this!"

436
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:27,210
- Grandpa, you got this!
- You got this!

437
00:26:34,384 --> 00:26:35,385
Go.

438
00:26:35,969 --> 00:26:37,220
Here you go.

439
00:26:37,304 --> 00:26:38,805
Be careful. It's hot.

440
00:26:40,432 --> 00:26:41,558
Coming.

441
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:44,019
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

442
00:26:49,024 --> 00:26:51,359
We finally have some customers today.

443
00:26:51,443 --> 00:26:52,944
Where in the world is that man?

444
00:26:57,240 --> 00:27:00,118
Hello, this is Ullala Chicken.

445
00:27:00,201 --> 00:27:01,536
Are they calling for a delivery?

446
00:27:04,247 --> 00:27:05,832
I'll take your order.

447
00:27:05,915 --> 00:27:07,459
I'm calling from
the Incheon Police Station.

448
00:27:07,542 --> 00:27:09,002
Is Mr. Hong Chun-seop there?

449
00:27:10,253 --> 00:27:12,047
That's my husband.

450
00:27:12,130 --> 00:27:13,131
What's this about?

451
00:27:13,214 --> 00:27:15,133
<i>I assume you're familiar</i>
<i>with Jemulpo Liquor Wholesale?</i>

452
00:27:15,216 --> 00:27:17,218
It went bankrupt as of yesterday,

453
00:27:17,302 --> 00:27:19,220
and the owner took his own life.

454
00:27:20,138 --> 00:27:23,475
<i>We are currently checking in</i>
<i>on the business owners</i>

455
00:27:23,558 --> 00:27:24,976
<i>who provided services on credit.</i>

456
00:27:25,060 --> 00:27:28,480
<i>We're trying to prevent</i>
<i>any unfortunate cascading incidents.</i>

457
00:27:38,198 --> 00:27:41,701
FUNERAL HALL

458
00:27:47,082 --> 00:27:49,042
Do you know how many times I paged you?

459
00:27:49,125 --> 00:27:50,960
Why didn't you call me back?

460
00:27:51,044 --> 00:27:53,380
Gosh, lower your voice.

461
00:27:53,463 --> 00:27:55,799
I sent you to collect money,
not mope around at a funeral.

462
00:27:55,882 --> 00:27:58,134
How could I ask for the money right now?

463
00:27:58,718 --> 00:28:01,221
We were classmates once,
and we were like brothers.

464
00:28:02,389 --> 00:28:04,099
I should at least send him off properly.

465
00:28:04,766 --> 00:28:05,767
Oh, right.

466
00:28:06,267 --> 00:28:08,853
If you have any cash on you,
could you give it to me?

467
00:28:08,937 --> 00:28:11,606
I wasn't able to give
condolence money earlier.

468
00:28:15,485 --> 00:28:17,237
Come on, just give me a little.

469
00:28:18,947 --> 00:28:20,532
Grandpa.

470
00:28:37,465 --> 00:28:41,010
I thought something terrible
had happened to you.

471
00:28:42,846 --> 00:28:45,181
Don't tell the kids
because they'll just get upset.

472
00:28:46,891 --> 00:28:49,978
Tell Grandpa to just worry about himself.

473
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:53,273
Grandpa, she says to worry about yourself.

474
00:28:54,691 --> 00:28:55,859
All right.

475
00:28:55,942 --> 00:28:56,776
Bom.

476
00:28:56,860 --> 00:28:58,570
You can't tell the aunties either, okay?

477
00:28:58,653 --> 00:28:59,863
Okay.

478
00:28:59,946 --> 00:29:03,032
And tell Grandma to stop scolding me.

479
00:29:03,616 --> 00:29:05,869
Grandpa says to stop scolding him.

480
00:29:05,952 --> 00:29:08,455
Tell him to stop giving me reason to.

481
00:29:08,538 --> 00:29:11,916
She says to stop giving her reason to.

482
00:29:14,627 --> 00:29:16,963
Oh, my back.

483
00:29:17,046 --> 00:29:19,340
{\an8}MOYUN HOSPITAL

484
00:29:20,258 --> 00:29:25,472
But still, Grandma and Grandpa
have become closer.

485
00:29:25,972 --> 00:29:29,350
Sometimes when we eat,
she passes him the side dishes…

486
00:29:31,644 --> 00:29:33,021
like this.

487
00:29:34,773 --> 00:29:36,649
You must've been worried.

488
00:29:36,733 --> 00:29:39,027
They said it was a secret,

489
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:41,696
but I thought you should know.

490
00:29:42,739 --> 00:29:46,034
You told me about Mommy, remember?

491
00:29:48,286 --> 00:29:49,329
Thank you.

492
00:29:50,914 --> 00:29:51,831
But Bom,

493
00:29:52,707 --> 00:29:55,126
I'll hold onto this
because it's dangerous.

494
00:29:55,210 --> 00:29:56,377
Okay.

495
00:30:04,010 --> 00:30:05,261
This one's for Mommy,

496
00:30:06,221 --> 00:30:07,847
and another for Mommy.

497
00:30:20,193 --> 00:30:22,862
{\an8}HANMIN HEIRESS KANG NORA
ENGAGED TO PRESIDENT SHIN JUNG-WOO

498
00:30:22,946 --> 00:30:26,241
{\an8}"CAN THERE BE TRUE LOVE
WHEN MONEY AND POWER MEET?"

499
00:30:36,543 --> 00:30:39,254
I assume this engagement announcement
was all your doing, ma'am?

500
00:30:40,129 --> 00:30:40,964
Did you see it?

501
00:30:41,047 --> 00:30:42,382
The photos came out nice, right?

502
00:30:42,465 --> 00:30:44,551
I put a lot of thought into the selection.

503
00:30:44,634 --> 00:30:45,760
<i>Didn't you agree</i>

504
00:30:45,844 --> 00:30:48,221
to discuss everything with me
before moving ahead?

505
00:30:48,304 --> 00:30:52,058
Ju-ran, just go along with me this once.

506
00:30:52,141 --> 00:30:54,644
If I left it up to you
with your already busy schedule,

507
00:30:54,727 --> 00:30:56,020
it would've taken forever and ever.

508
00:30:56,104 --> 00:30:58,481
<i>When exactly would I see Nora</i>
<i>in a wedding dress?</i>

509
00:30:59,023 --> 00:31:01,234
Weddings are my specialty.

510
00:31:01,317 --> 00:31:03,862
I'm an expert with three under my belt.

511
00:31:05,697 --> 00:31:06,781
Would you dare to say

512
00:31:07,282 --> 00:31:09,868
those exact words
in front of the chairman?

513
00:31:09,951 --> 00:31:12,662
You're always so quick
to threaten me with the chairman.

514
00:31:13,246 --> 00:31:15,373
It's getting old.
Change up your repertoire.

515
00:31:16,499 --> 00:31:17,500
What a joke.

516
00:31:21,921 --> 00:31:24,090
{\an8}HANMIN HEIRESS KANG NORA
ENGAGED TO PRESIDENT SHIN JUNG-WOO

517
00:31:26,718 --> 00:31:28,511
What does this mean for their family tree?

518
00:31:29,095 --> 00:31:31,306
The president would become
the chairman's second son-in-law

519
00:31:31,389 --> 00:31:33,391
and Executive Director Oh's
younger brother-in-law.

520
00:31:33,975 --> 00:31:35,602
As for Big Al, he'd be…

521
00:31:35,685 --> 00:31:36,519
the uncle?

522
00:31:37,478 --> 00:31:40,440
Before all that,
he'd be Ms. Kang's husband.

523
00:31:40,523 --> 00:31:43,276
No wonder they've had
dinner together so often lately.

524
00:31:43,902 --> 00:31:47,363
But shouldn't they set up
their own dates and meet up?

525
00:31:47,447 --> 00:31:48,740
Why do they have you do it?

526
00:31:50,241 --> 00:31:51,367
You're right.

527
00:31:52,243 --> 00:31:53,870
Let's stay focused on the task at hand.

528
00:31:54,871 --> 00:31:57,165
We will make another call
at exactly 9 p.m. tonight.

529
00:31:58,207 --> 00:31:59,208
- Mr. Lee.
- Yes?

530
00:31:59,292 --> 00:32:02,253
- You made some nice <i>gimbap </i>rolls.
- Thank you.

531
00:32:02,337 --> 00:32:03,796
Have some,

532
00:32:04,380 --> 00:32:05,423
ma'am.

533
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:08,593
Sure.

534
00:32:11,137 --> 00:32:13,723
Ms. Go, you can finish that first

535
00:32:13,806 --> 00:32:15,516
and move on to the next container.

536
00:32:21,814 --> 00:32:23,775
Have you considered our proposal?

537
00:32:27,570 --> 00:32:30,990
Well, you see,
I'd be taking a huge risk here.

538
00:32:31,074 --> 00:32:34,911
{\an8}<i>Shin Jung-woo, the young executive,</i>
<i>is to marry into Hanmin.</i>

539
00:32:34,994 --> 00:32:38,581
His fiancée is Kang Nora,
the only daughter of Chairman Kang.

540
00:32:39,499 --> 00:32:42,251
They need to issue
a correction for that article.

541
00:32:42,335 --> 00:32:43,753
"The only daughter"?

542
00:32:43,836 --> 00:32:46,506
Our chairman had one son
and two daughters,

543
00:32:46,589 --> 00:32:48,299
and I'm his eldest son-in-law, all right?

544
00:32:49,550 --> 00:32:51,719
I wondered if I'd chosen
the wrong person for the job.

545
00:32:51,803 --> 00:32:54,472
Come on now. There's no need for all that.

546
00:32:54,555 --> 00:32:56,099
You definitely chose the right person.

547
00:32:56,808 --> 00:32:57,642
Just a second.

548
00:32:58,893 --> 00:32:59,811
Ten billion won.

549
00:33:01,145 --> 00:33:01,980
Ten billion.

550
00:33:03,231 --> 00:33:04,774
Let's go for it. Let's do it.

551
00:33:05,525 --> 00:33:06,442
<i>But this time,</i>

552
00:33:06,526 --> 00:33:08,361
I want this deal made face-to-face.

553
00:33:13,282 --> 00:33:14,158
All right.

554
00:33:15,118 --> 00:33:16,703
<i>The deal will take place tomorrow night.</i>

555
00:33:16,786 --> 00:33:20,039
I'll be in touch
with the exact time and place.

556
00:33:23,292 --> 00:33:24,460
What now?

557
00:33:24,544 --> 00:33:25,837
What do we do?

558
00:33:31,843 --> 00:33:32,802
Good choice.

559
00:33:34,053 --> 00:33:36,014
It's just one day.

560
00:33:36,097 --> 00:33:38,474
I'll borrow it just for one day
and return it.

561
00:33:39,434 --> 00:33:41,144
Let's just go for it, damn it.

562
00:33:41,769 --> 00:33:44,022
Ten billion won.

563
00:33:44,897 --> 00:33:47,233
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES
MAGANG BRANCH

564
00:33:47,316 --> 00:33:48,192
{\an8}BRANCH MANAGER KIM MUN-HO

565
00:33:48,276 --> 00:33:49,318
{\an8}Sir.

566
00:33:49,402 --> 00:33:52,155
We can't cover such a large sum
without prior notice.

567
00:33:52,655 --> 00:33:54,949
We don't even keep
ten billion won in the vault.

568
00:33:55,533 --> 00:33:56,576
Gosh.

569
00:33:57,285 --> 00:33:58,286
Hey.

570
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:01,414
Do you think I only came
to the Magang Branch?

571
00:34:01,497 --> 00:34:03,583
All the other branches
came through without excuses.

572
00:34:04,917 --> 00:34:07,086
You're surprisingly unambitious,
aren't you?

573
00:34:07,670 --> 00:34:09,839
Do you want to stay
a branch manager forever?

574
00:34:10,339 --> 00:34:12,258
What do you think will happen
once I become the chairman?

575
00:34:12,341 --> 00:34:14,469
The first thing I'll do
is an organizational reshuffle.

576
00:34:15,386 --> 00:34:16,220
Goodness.

577
00:34:16,721 --> 00:34:18,306
Don't worry, you'll be fine.

578
00:34:20,099 --> 00:34:21,267
This coffee tastes great.

579
00:34:21,350 --> 00:34:22,393
Go ahead and load it up.

580
00:34:48,127 --> 00:34:49,128
Here he comes.

581
00:34:52,673 --> 00:34:53,674
He came by himself.

582
00:34:59,972 --> 00:35:01,057
Let's get started.

583
00:35:05,311 --> 00:35:07,480
Jeez, this place looks haunted.

584
00:35:08,689 --> 00:35:10,358
Why meet here, of all places?

585
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:12,985
My goodness.

586
00:35:30,586 --> 00:35:33,840
<i>Here's to striking gold</i>
<i>Striking gold</i>

587
00:35:34,507 --> 00:35:37,885
This place is probably empty,
day and night.

588
00:35:37,969 --> 00:35:40,054
Why did they have to meet at night?

589
00:35:42,140 --> 00:35:43,474
There we go.

590
00:35:48,104 --> 00:35:49,522
Yes, I've arrived.

591
00:35:49,605 --> 00:35:51,691
Where have you arrived exactly?

592
00:35:52,650 --> 00:35:54,610
- Chairman?
- Where are you?

593
00:35:55,194 --> 00:35:57,321
<i>I told you to keep a low profile</i>

594
00:35:57,405 --> 00:36:00,241
because there are
sharp eyes watching everywhere!

595
00:36:00,825 --> 00:36:01,951
Also,

596
00:36:02,493 --> 00:36:04,620
Albert has been coming home late recently.

597
00:36:05,288 --> 00:36:06,247
Yes, right.

598
00:36:06,831 --> 00:36:09,041
I've come to drop by a funeral, sir.

599
00:36:09,125 --> 00:36:11,711
I'll pick up Albert and be home soon.

600
00:36:11,794 --> 00:36:13,379
Unbelievable.

601
00:36:15,548 --> 00:36:16,883
He gives me a headache.

602
00:36:19,343 --> 00:36:20,887
Aside from Assemblyman Song,

603
00:36:20,970 --> 00:36:23,806
has anyone else called
about not getting their interest payments?

604
00:36:23,890 --> 00:36:24,974
Not yet, sir.

605
00:36:26,058 --> 00:36:26,893
All right.

606
00:36:29,270 --> 00:36:32,857
I casually asked
as I sent them New Year's gifts,

607
00:36:32,940 --> 00:36:34,734
and a few of them
were under the impression

608
00:36:34,817 --> 00:36:37,486
that our financial situation
was to blame for the delays.

609
00:36:37,570 --> 00:36:39,697
It appears that was
Executive Director Oh's excuse.

610
00:36:41,532 --> 00:36:43,284
Oh Deok-gyu…

611
00:36:43,784 --> 00:36:48,956
He's been such a reliable deliveryman
for 20 years without a single issue.

612
00:36:49,707 --> 00:36:50,750
Then again,

613
00:36:50,833 --> 00:36:54,587
the mere sight of money fuels greed.

614
00:36:54,670 --> 00:36:56,047
{\an8}LUCKY APPLES

615
00:37:03,638 --> 00:37:05,473
Jeez, what was that?

616
00:37:10,728 --> 00:37:14,357
Hey, I've arrived
and entered the building.

617
00:37:15,233 --> 00:37:16,692
I think I'm at the right place.

618
00:37:16,776 --> 00:37:18,444
<i>Why didn't you answer your phone?</i>

619
00:37:19,028 --> 00:37:21,447
<i>If you shared this with anyone else…</i>

620
00:37:21,530 --> 00:37:24,659
No, it's not like that.
I just got a call from home.

621
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:27,787
But where are you exactly?

622
00:37:30,331 --> 00:37:31,499
Hello?

623
00:37:33,376 --> 00:37:34,794
Anyone here?

624
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:39,674
Oh, my eyes.

625
00:37:44,136 --> 00:37:45,888
Hey, you don't want to hurt me.

626
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:52,979
All disguised, I see.

627
00:37:59,735 --> 00:38:01,112
<i>Everything has been confirmed.</i>

628
00:38:01,195 --> 00:38:03,030
<i>You can check the gift</i>
<i>we've prepared for you.</i>

629
00:38:03,114 --> 00:38:04,156
All right.

630
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:05,700
Be gentle, okay?

631
00:38:09,787 --> 00:38:10,705
Must you hold me like this?

632
00:38:31,142 --> 00:38:32,143
Let go of me.

633
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:40,026
My goodness.

634
00:38:40,109 --> 00:38:41,569
So this is ten billion won, huh?

635
00:38:45,573 --> 00:38:47,241
It's so crisp.

636
00:38:51,495 --> 00:38:52,830
Good work, everyone.

637
00:38:53,414 --> 00:38:54,332
Thanks.

638
00:39:04,592 --> 00:39:06,594
Be careful now.

639
00:39:07,970 --> 00:39:08,971
There you go.

640
00:39:10,431 --> 00:39:13,476
You're awfully weak for supposed crooks.

641
00:39:14,602 --> 00:39:16,228
I mean, thank you for your efforts.

642
00:39:19,648 --> 00:39:21,067
Make sure they don't rip.

643
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:23,361
There you go.

644
00:39:26,822 --> 00:39:28,282
Hold on a second.

645
00:39:28,366 --> 00:39:29,784
My arms have gone numb.

646
00:40:38,060 --> 00:40:39,478
I'll pocket just the five billion

647
00:40:39,979 --> 00:40:41,230
and return the principal

648
00:40:41,856 --> 00:40:44,275
to the Magang Branch immediately.

649
00:40:55,286 --> 00:40:56,454
Man, it's heavy.

650
00:40:59,331 --> 00:41:00,583
To make money,

651
00:41:01,876 --> 00:41:03,669
you've got to be smart

652
00:41:04,295 --> 00:41:05,713
and diligent.

653
00:41:06,297 --> 00:41:07,506
That's…

654
00:41:13,679 --> 00:41:15,556
Wait, why are these…

655
00:41:28,319 --> 00:41:29,403
Why is this…

656
00:41:46,712 --> 00:41:50,508
You bastards!

657
00:41:53,219 --> 00:41:55,221
Damn it.

658
00:42:00,434 --> 00:42:03,187
Where is all this money
coming from anyway?

659
00:42:04,271 --> 00:42:06,357
He must've figured it out by now, right?

660
00:42:07,191 --> 00:42:08,150
Could he have reported it?

661
00:42:09,485 --> 00:42:11,153
My dad wouldn't report it.

662
00:42:11,946 --> 00:42:13,656
I'm sure he'll try to
clean up the mess though.

663
00:42:13,739 --> 00:42:14,698
Are you worried?

664
00:42:16,534 --> 00:42:18,786
I knew he wouldn't recognize me,

665
00:42:18,869 --> 00:42:21,163
but seeing that he didn't
even with me right in front of him,

666
00:42:22,164 --> 00:42:22,998
upsets me.

667
00:42:24,458 --> 00:42:26,168
So you were upset.

668
00:42:26,710 --> 00:42:28,712
We need to kick him out. Leave, Big Al.

669
00:42:29,630 --> 00:42:32,883
I'm just sharing my feelings and emotions
with the team.

670
00:42:34,051 --> 00:42:36,053
From this point on,
I have the biggest part to play.

671
00:42:36,136 --> 00:42:37,096
You're right.

672
00:42:37,596 --> 00:42:39,348
It's all up to you now, Big Al.

673
00:42:43,894 --> 00:42:46,605
Now, we're entering the third phase.

674
00:42:49,149 --> 00:42:51,402
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

675
00:43:01,370 --> 00:43:03,247
Did you need to tell me something?

676
00:43:05,874 --> 00:43:07,876
Well, you see, yesterday…

677
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:10,796
I experienced something strange.

678
00:43:12,548 --> 00:43:15,593
I heard scammers are reaching out
to senior executives

679
00:43:17,011 --> 00:43:20,389
in the financial sector
to pull off major scams.

680
00:43:22,558 --> 00:43:23,892
And well,

681
00:43:23,976 --> 00:43:26,437
you're still new to how things work
in Korea nowadays.

682
00:43:27,146 --> 00:43:28,731
That's why.

683
00:43:28,814 --> 00:43:30,649
I was just worried about you, that's all.

684
00:43:32,526 --> 00:43:35,613
Only a select few know my personal line.

685
00:43:35,696 --> 00:43:37,573
Right, me too.

686
00:43:39,241 --> 00:43:40,784
<i>Should I ask him for some money?</i>

687
00:43:41,535 --> 00:43:42,494
<i>No.</i>

688
00:43:42,578 --> 00:43:44,413
<i>Who would lend me ten billion won?</i>

689
00:43:46,707 --> 00:43:47,750
Hey, President Shin.

690
00:43:48,959 --> 00:43:50,377
Do you know someone named "K"?

691
00:43:51,712 --> 00:43:52,713
"K"?

692
00:43:56,258 --> 00:43:58,260
I ought to treat you today.

693
00:43:59,094 --> 00:44:02,222
This place might not look like much,
but it's quite good.

694
00:44:02,306 --> 00:44:04,058
It's an excellent restaurant
by my standards.

695
00:44:07,102 --> 00:44:07,936
It's delicious.

696
00:44:08,020 --> 00:44:09,063
Gosh.

697
00:44:09,897 --> 00:44:11,398
You're even so down-to-earth.

698
00:44:14,777 --> 00:44:18,030
Well, why the sudden lunch call?

699
00:44:18,530 --> 00:44:20,407
You wouldn't ask to meet without a reason.

700
00:44:21,867 --> 00:44:23,452
Is it regarding…

701
00:44:24,161 --> 00:44:25,120
the Hong we know?

702
00:44:27,456 --> 00:44:30,584
Have you heard of someone who goes by "K"?

703
00:44:30,668 --> 00:44:31,502
"K"?

704
00:44:32,544 --> 00:44:33,629
As in the letter K?

705
00:44:34,463 --> 00:44:36,965
When we met for dinner
with Executive Director Oh,

706
00:44:37,758 --> 00:44:40,344
you mentioned an issue
regarding the exchange of old banknotes.

707
00:44:41,178 --> 00:44:43,722
You said scammers were contacting
people in the financial sector

708
00:44:43,806 --> 00:44:46,392
under the guise of old banknote exchanges…

709
00:44:51,897 --> 00:44:53,982
- Here you go.
- Pardon me.

710
00:44:58,862 --> 00:45:00,364
Let me hear the reason.

711
00:45:00,989 --> 00:45:02,658
Why are you asking me about that?

712
00:45:04,076 --> 00:45:06,662
That Nam Dong-gi
also mentioned this before.

713
00:45:07,454 --> 00:45:10,332
Ever since the failed probe
into Hanmin's slush fund,

714
00:45:10,916 --> 00:45:14,378
Keum-bo's standing within the FSS
has diminished, hasn't it?

715
00:45:15,421 --> 00:45:17,423
Well, I guess we could say that.

716
00:45:18,465 --> 00:45:21,427
If the FSS is waiting for tips,

717
00:45:21,510 --> 00:45:25,472
could she be reinstated after she catches
this financial criminal named "K"?

718
00:45:25,556 --> 00:45:28,142
I'll gladly assist in crafting
such a pretext for her return.

719
00:45:28,225 --> 00:45:29,309
I see.

720
00:45:30,185 --> 00:45:32,521
So it was because of Hong, after all.

721
00:45:32,604 --> 00:45:35,232
You just want her gone
as soon as possible.

722
00:45:35,315 --> 00:45:37,776
It's only a matter of time
before Hanmin falls.

723
00:45:37,860 --> 00:45:40,320
The tree will soon die on its own,

724
00:45:40,404 --> 00:45:43,157
so there's no need for her
to try knocking it down by herself.

725
00:45:44,158 --> 00:45:47,035
Please try to persuade her.

726
00:46:00,340 --> 00:46:04,344
When you've grown up with someone
and stayed close for a long time,

727
00:46:04,428 --> 00:46:06,013
you're prone to misreading them.

728
00:46:07,806 --> 00:46:09,725
My little brother was like that to me.

729
00:46:09,808 --> 00:46:11,810
I thought I knew him so well.

730
00:46:13,103 --> 00:46:15,105
Even when we were all grown up,

731
00:46:16,106 --> 00:46:19,610
I still saw him as a child
and was busy getting angry at him.

732
00:46:21,153 --> 00:46:23,197
I thought he'd always listen to me.

733
00:46:25,491 --> 00:46:27,784
{\an8}9 YEARS AGO, 1988

734
00:46:27,868 --> 00:46:28,785
{\an8}Damn it!

735
00:46:31,121 --> 00:46:32,289
Hey.

736
00:46:32,372 --> 00:46:35,959
Why did you get tangled up with Hanmin
and make this mess?

737
00:46:36,043 --> 00:46:37,419
Just walk away.

738
00:46:37,503 --> 00:46:39,087
No, just quit your job.

739
00:46:39,171 --> 00:46:40,297
You punk!

740
00:46:43,175 --> 00:46:45,969
You should've kept your mouth shut
for your brother's sake.

741
00:46:51,642 --> 00:46:53,352
To the advancement of Korea

742
00:46:53,435 --> 00:46:55,646
and the successful closing
of the Olympic Games!

743
00:46:55,729 --> 00:46:57,064
Cheers!

744
00:46:57,147 --> 00:46:59,066
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

745
00:46:59,149 --> 00:47:01,318
- Great work.
- Thank you. You too.

746
00:47:05,280 --> 00:47:07,032
Sir, let me pour you a drink.

747
00:47:07,115 --> 00:47:10,244
<i>The police announced the results</i>
<i>of the Hanmin accounting fraud case,</i>

748
00:47:10,327 --> 00:47:12,704
<i>stating that an employee of Hanmin,</i>
<i>identified as Mr. Kim,</i>

749
00:47:12,788 --> 00:47:14,748
<i>had deliberately manipulated the accounts.</i>

750
00:47:14,831 --> 00:47:18,752
<i>It was carried out in collusion</i>
<i>with Mr. Yun, an external accountant,</i>

751
00:47:18,835 --> 00:47:20,546
<i>in order to conceal his embezzlement.</i>

752
00:47:21,046 --> 00:47:24,466
<i>Mr. Yun, the accountant</i>
<i>who was being investigated by the police,</i>

753
00:47:24,550 --> 00:47:26,760
<i>committed suicide</i>
<i>by jumping from his apartment building</i>

754
00:47:26,843 --> 00:47:27,886
<i>around 3 p.m. today.</i>

755
00:47:28,470 --> 00:47:29,805
<i>Following the report of the incident,</i>

756
00:47:29,888 --> 00:47:33,100
<i>the police collected</i>
<i>Mr. Yun's notes and personal effects…</i>

757
00:47:34,476 --> 00:47:36,979
The last person my brother called

758
00:47:38,480 --> 00:47:39,648
was me.

759
00:47:40,899 --> 00:47:42,359
When he did,

760
00:47:42,442 --> 00:47:43,652
I hounded him,

761
00:47:44,194 --> 00:47:45,237
scolded him,

762
00:47:46,572 --> 00:47:48,282
and told him he was naive.

763
00:47:49,241 --> 00:47:50,826
I yelled and cursed him out.

764
00:47:52,661 --> 00:47:55,664
A part of me was worried about him,
but the truth is,

765
00:47:56,164 --> 00:47:57,666
I was worried it could hurt me.

766
00:47:59,084 --> 00:48:00,586
I was more worried about myself.

767
00:48:04,339 --> 00:48:06,174
It became a lasting regret.

768
00:48:14,725 --> 00:48:16,143
You must have…

769
00:48:16,935 --> 00:48:18,770
similar regret.

770
00:48:21,648 --> 00:48:22,524
Yes.

771
00:48:23,233 --> 00:48:24,234
I do.

772
00:48:26,737 --> 00:48:27,654
You could be…

773
00:48:29,072 --> 00:48:33,076
seeing Hong Keum-bo
the way you did nine years ago.

774
00:48:35,495 --> 00:48:36,913
Let's just wait and see.

775
00:48:42,044 --> 00:48:44,713
You should eat up
before the soup gets cold.

776
00:49:09,821 --> 00:49:11,907
I'm working up the courage
to go up to the 12th floor.

777
00:49:14,242 --> 00:49:15,619
Are you still upset?

778
00:49:16,745 --> 00:49:17,621
A little.

779
00:49:18,580 --> 00:49:21,667
Reality is definitely different
from what I anticipated.

780
00:49:24,211 --> 00:49:26,296
I guess since Mr. Oh Deok-gyu is family,

781
00:49:27,839 --> 00:49:29,883
I hoped he would be different
from my grandfather.

782
00:49:32,594 --> 00:49:34,388
Although it wasn't family,

783
00:49:35,222 --> 00:49:38,016
I was once deeply disappointed
by someone I trusted and relied on.

784
00:49:39,810 --> 00:49:42,979
Even when everyone was hounding me
with the same old line,

785
00:49:44,189 --> 00:49:45,857
I had hoped he'd be different.

786
00:49:46,441 --> 00:49:47,484
But he was just the same?

787
00:49:51,113 --> 00:49:51,947
What about now?

788
00:49:53,323 --> 00:49:54,449
Do you regret it?

789
00:49:55,701 --> 00:49:56,535
I don't.

790
00:49:57,911 --> 00:49:59,788
That's why I'm working extra hard now,

791
00:50:00,372 --> 00:50:02,999
so my future self doesn't regret it.

792
00:50:05,544 --> 00:50:06,503
Your future self?

793
00:50:47,544 --> 00:50:48,795
What are you doing, Dad?

794
00:50:48,879 --> 00:50:49,880
It's time to go home.

795
00:50:52,007 --> 00:50:53,967
Grandpa's been checking attendance lately.

796
00:50:55,594 --> 00:50:57,220
Looks like I'll lose points again.

797
00:50:58,847 --> 00:50:59,890
What is it?

798
00:51:03,727 --> 00:51:06,313
Dad, you have to be honest with me.

799
00:51:07,272 --> 00:51:08,523
We're family.

800
00:51:14,488 --> 00:51:15,614
Oh gosh.

801
00:51:19,075 --> 00:51:22,037
<i>The Magang Branch Manager</i>
<i>is calling for you, sir.</i>

802
00:51:26,750 --> 00:51:27,918
Damn it.

803
00:51:41,389 --> 00:51:42,724
Dad.

804
00:51:44,351 --> 00:51:45,393
Dad!

805
00:51:48,522 --> 00:51:49,940
You have to tell me what's going on.

806
00:52:00,492 --> 00:52:02,285
I should come clean…

807
00:52:03,578 --> 00:52:04,955
to the chairman, right?

808
00:52:07,833 --> 00:52:10,252
You just need to return the money
without him knowing.

809
00:52:11,711 --> 00:52:12,546
Dad.

810
00:52:13,630 --> 00:52:14,631
There's only one way out of this.

811
00:52:15,257 --> 00:52:16,424
What is it?

812
00:52:16,508 --> 00:52:17,467
Do you have money?

813
00:52:17,551 --> 00:52:19,427
You know I don't.

814
00:52:21,137 --> 00:52:22,347
But you have stocks.

815
00:52:23,390 --> 00:52:24,224
The company stocks.

816
00:52:24,307 --> 00:52:26,601
If I sell those,
what about my shares of the company?

817
00:52:26,685 --> 00:52:28,812
If I become the successor, the chairman,

818
00:52:29,771 --> 00:52:30,814
it won't be an issue.

819
00:52:32,858 --> 00:52:34,568
Isn't that the future you want?

820
00:52:36,403 --> 00:52:37,237
It is.

821
00:52:41,575 --> 00:52:42,993
Let's put out the immediate fire first.

822
00:52:47,038 --> 00:52:48,123
All right.

823
00:52:59,134 --> 00:53:00,635
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES HTS

824
00:53:04,890 --> 00:53:06,683
By the way, who will own those stocks?

825
00:53:06,766 --> 00:53:08,059
Yeouido Pirates will.

826
00:53:08,852 --> 00:53:11,187
We officially registered
as an investment firm yesterday.

827
00:53:11,271 --> 00:53:12,898
Big Al was the captain
of the online community,

828
00:53:12,981 --> 00:53:15,358
but the CEO of the investment firm
is Ms. Hong Keum-bo.

829
00:53:15,442 --> 00:53:16,401
We're all one team now.

830
00:53:16,484 --> 00:53:17,986
Isn't the name a bit obvious?

831
00:53:18,069 --> 00:53:19,195
Yes, and intentionally so.

832
00:53:19,946 --> 00:53:23,825
I can only keep watch
until the president returns at noon.

833
00:53:23,909 --> 00:53:25,118
I'm going to place the buy order,

834
00:53:25,201 --> 00:53:26,995
and just come back
to check when it's time.

835
00:53:29,915 --> 00:53:31,416
STOCK BUY ORDER
CONFIRM

836
00:53:43,637 --> 00:53:46,139
Now, we're entering the third phase.

837
00:53:46,222 --> 00:53:47,515
{\an8}OH DEOK-GYU 9%

838
00:53:47,599 --> 00:53:49,559
{\an8}Gradually sell through program trading,

839
00:53:50,352 --> 00:53:53,146
so we can absorb it all
at the agreed time.

840
00:53:58,735 --> 00:54:00,195
I'm the head of Trading.

841
00:54:01,237 --> 00:54:02,197
I'll sell it off carefully…

842
00:54:03,490 --> 00:54:04,574
just a bit at a time,

843
00:54:05,825 --> 00:54:06,701
under the radar.

844
00:54:07,827 --> 00:54:08,954
My son…

845
00:54:09,037 --> 00:54:10,372
You're all grown up now.

846
00:54:10,455 --> 00:54:11,373
Thank you.

847
00:54:14,042 --> 00:54:16,252
When did the stock price drop this much?

848
00:54:17,295 --> 00:54:18,546
Damn it, my money.

849
00:54:19,881 --> 00:54:21,591
My precious money…

850
00:54:22,676 --> 00:54:24,260
I'm about to lose it.

851
00:54:27,764 --> 00:54:29,891
Where is the buyer's IP traced to?

852
00:54:29,975 --> 00:54:31,309
I used an IP proxy,

853
00:54:31,393 --> 00:54:33,186
so it'll show up as the 12th floor.

854
00:54:34,229 --> 00:54:38,483
Based on my simulations,
we should be able to buy up about 99%.

855
00:54:52,539 --> 00:54:59,462
{\an8}OH DEOK-GYU'S SHARES,
YEOUIDO PIRATES' SHARES

856
00:54:59,546 --> 00:55:02,674
{\an8}OH DEOK-GYU'S SHARES,
YEOUIDO PIRATES' SHARES

857
00:55:02,757 --> 00:55:04,384
{\an8}TRANSACTION COMPLETE

858
00:55:05,593 --> 00:55:07,429
- It's done. We got it.
- We did it!

859
00:55:08,471 --> 00:55:11,725
We really did it!

860
00:55:13,351 --> 00:55:14,519
{\an8}3 DAYS LATER

861
00:55:14,602 --> 00:55:15,478
{\an8}My apologies, sir.

862
00:55:16,021 --> 00:55:17,856
{\an8}There was a bit of a delay
with the briefing.

863
00:55:18,565 --> 00:55:20,483
The interest payments
for the 1997 fiscal year

864
00:55:20,567 --> 00:55:24,237
owed to the 12 assembly members
have all been completed.

865
00:55:24,821 --> 00:55:25,697
Good.

866
00:55:26,364 --> 00:55:27,407
Well done.

867
00:55:28,742 --> 00:55:30,201
Going forward…

868
00:55:30,285 --> 00:55:31,119
Yes?

869
00:55:35,415 --> 00:55:38,126
- Get home early.
- Yes, sir.

870
00:55:38,209 --> 00:55:40,670
These chances to sit down together
for a family dinner

871
00:55:40,754 --> 00:55:42,255
won't last forever.

872
00:55:42,964 --> 00:55:43,798
Yes, sir.

873
00:55:44,340 --> 00:55:45,341
I'll keep that in mind.

874
00:55:47,510 --> 00:55:48,428
All right.

875
00:55:58,897 --> 00:56:01,274
Should I look into
why it took over a week?

876
00:56:01,357 --> 00:56:02,400
No need.

877
00:56:02,484 --> 00:56:03,860
Leave it.

878
00:56:03,943 --> 00:56:06,362
Let's not stir up trouble.

879
00:56:07,989 --> 00:56:11,201
Let's just focus on
figuring out the best ways

880
00:56:11,284 --> 00:56:15,205
to use the slush funds entrusted to us
by the assembly members.

881
00:56:31,513 --> 00:56:33,098
Executive Director Oh Deok-gyu.

882
00:56:34,641 --> 00:56:37,268
He definitely had some money troubles.

883
00:56:54,661 --> 00:56:55,870
<i>But you have stocks.</i>

884
00:56:57,205 --> 00:56:58,081
<i>The company stocks.</i>

885
00:56:58,164 --> 00:57:00,166
<i>If I sell those,</i>
<i>what about my shares of the company?</i>

886
00:57:00,250 --> 00:57:02,252
<i>If I become the successor, the chairman,</i>

887
00:57:03,419 --> 00:57:04,504
<i>it won't be an issue.</i>

888
00:57:17,058 --> 00:57:18,143
Mr. Cha.

889
00:57:18,935 --> 00:57:20,395
This is Song Ju-ran.

890
00:57:21,020 --> 00:57:22,147
I need something checked.

891
00:57:24,065 --> 00:57:25,733
Can you check on something for me?

892
00:57:38,621 --> 00:57:42,125
As you requested, I checked on
Executive Director Oh's company shares.

893
00:57:42,208 --> 00:57:44,127
That took longer than expected.

894
00:57:44,210 --> 00:57:46,504
Yes, I wanted to make sure
it wasn't some sort of error.

895
00:57:47,297 --> 00:57:48,715
I verified it at least five times.

896
00:57:50,133 --> 00:57:51,176
Executive Director Oh…

897
00:57:52,760 --> 00:57:54,429
has in his possession

898
00:57:55,013 --> 00:57:56,473
one share of Hanmin stock.

899
00:57:59,642 --> 00:58:00,477
One share?

900
00:58:01,603 --> 00:58:02,479
Yes.

901
00:58:04,314 --> 00:58:08,568
Why did he sell off all his shares?

902
00:58:11,070 --> 00:58:12,280
Are you asking me?

903
00:58:13,990 --> 00:58:14,824
No, ma'am.

904
00:58:17,160 --> 00:58:19,537
I'll report this to the chairman myself.

905
00:58:21,664 --> 00:58:23,708
You must not tell anyone about this

906
00:58:25,001 --> 00:58:26,878
until the chairman orders otherwise.

907
00:58:26,961 --> 00:58:28,087
Yes, of course.

908
00:58:28,171 --> 00:58:29,964
I have that much sense.

909
00:58:45,104 --> 00:58:48,066
I must keep my mouth shut.

910
00:58:52,529 --> 00:58:54,489
Executive Director Oh is out,
that's for sure.

911
00:58:55,949 --> 00:58:58,409
I'd better cancel the order
for his New Year's gift.

912
00:59:09,295 --> 00:59:10,421
Why aren't you going in?

913
00:59:13,341 --> 00:59:15,385
The chairman asked you
to refrain from visiting the offices.

914
00:59:15,468 --> 00:59:16,803
Did you forget already?

915
00:59:16,886 --> 00:59:19,722
He and I had a private chat after that.

916
00:59:19,806 --> 00:59:22,892
I'm here to have lunch with him and Nora
together as a family.

917
00:59:22,976 --> 00:59:24,102
Can you step aside?

918
00:59:35,655 --> 00:59:37,782
She's not the type to back down so easily.

919
00:59:38,992 --> 00:59:40,201
What's going on?

920
00:59:41,119 --> 00:59:42,328
Don't just stand there. Open the door.

921
00:59:45,456 --> 00:59:46,457
Chairman.

922
00:59:47,041 --> 00:59:47,917
Enjoy.

923
00:59:49,460 --> 00:59:50,753
Let's see.

924
00:59:50,837 --> 00:59:53,548
I know we eat breakfast together
every morning,

925
00:59:54,132 --> 00:59:56,509
but it can get so crowded at home.

926
00:59:56,593 --> 01:00:00,138
It's nice to have lunch
with just the three of us.

927
01:00:00,221 --> 01:00:01,055
Don't you agree?

928
01:00:02,432 --> 01:00:03,474
Let's see here.

929
01:00:06,185 --> 01:00:07,020
Eat up.

930
01:00:10,857 --> 01:00:12,275
It's not bad.

931
01:00:12,358 --> 01:00:14,444
- It's good, right?
- Yes.

932
01:00:19,991 --> 01:00:22,243
LET'S GATHER OUR GOLD
AND UNITE IN PURPOSE FOR OUR ECONOMY

933
01:00:22,327 --> 01:00:26,581
<i>"The Gold Collection Campaign to Overcome</i>
<i>the IMF Foreign Exchange Crisis."</i>

934
01:00:26,664 --> 01:00:29,542
<i>I'm reporting live from the scene.</i>
<i>Standing here, you can feel…</i>

935
01:00:29,626 --> 01:00:31,044
Ridiculous.

936
01:00:32,337 --> 01:00:33,838
There's an old saying

937
01:00:34,714 --> 01:00:38,468
that even a king
can't save his country from poverty.

938
01:00:39,552 --> 01:00:40,845
Just how could the people

939
01:00:41,679 --> 01:00:43,973
save the country from poverty?

940
01:00:44,766 --> 01:00:47,560
My goodness, what a naive idea.

941
01:00:47,644 --> 01:00:48,811
Absolutely.

942
01:00:48,895 --> 01:00:52,190
A great task like that
should be led by someone great like you,

943
01:00:52,273 --> 01:00:54,734
- don't you agree?
- My goodness.

944
01:00:58,946 --> 01:01:00,948
{\an8}COLLECTION POINT:
DONGYANG DEPARTMENT STORE

945
01:01:01,032 --> 01:01:03,743
GOLD COLLECTION CAMPAIGN

946
01:01:11,584 --> 01:01:13,002
GOLD COLLECTION CAMPAIGN

947
01:01:23,012 --> 01:01:25,682
{\an8}SAVE THE ECONOMY WITH UNUSED GOLD
MAGANG DISTRICT OFFICE

948
01:01:28,267 --> 01:01:29,727
<i>I see you brought your whole family.</i>

949
01:01:29,811 --> 01:01:31,187
What brings you here today?

950
01:01:31,270 --> 01:01:35,108
Well, we're just trying to do our part
to save the country.

951
01:01:35,191 --> 01:01:36,984
<i>Yes, there are many people here today.</i>

952
01:01:37,068 --> 01:01:39,487
<i>I think it's heartwarming</i>
<i>to see all these people gathered.</i>

953
01:01:39,570 --> 01:01:40,613
<i>Absolutely.</i>

954
01:01:42,782 --> 01:01:44,200
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

955
01:01:44,951 --> 01:01:46,411
I brought my kids' first birthday rings.

956
01:01:49,580 --> 01:01:51,708
I guess I wrapped it too tightly.

957
01:01:57,714 --> 01:01:59,757
And we have another touching moment here.

958
01:01:59,841 --> 01:02:01,592
A little girl has come all this way

959
01:02:01,676 --> 01:02:05,471
to willingly give up
her first birthday ring.

960
01:02:06,013 --> 01:02:08,891
How does it feel
to take part in this meaningful event?

961
01:02:08,975 --> 01:02:09,976
It's nice.

962
01:02:10,059 --> 01:02:12,019
Can I ask what made you want to come?

963
01:02:12,103 --> 01:02:16,065
Because we need to collect gold
to save our country.

964
01:02:16,149 --> 01:02:18,109
How amazing. Thank you.

965
01:02:18,192 --> 01:02:20,528
Thank you so much for taking part
in this meaningful event.

966
01:02:20,611 --> 01:02:22,530
Thank you. Take care.

967
01:02:23,573 --> 01:02:24,657
You want to interview me?

968
01:02:24,741 --> 01:02:26,200
Are you okay with it being broadcast live?

969
01:02:26,284 --> 01:02:28,494
- Yes, of course.
- Sure, I'd love to interview you.

970
01:02:29,412 --> 01:02:30,455
<i>Hello.</i>

971
01:02:31,038 --> 01:02:32,415
<i>I'm Hong Chun-seop,</i>

972
01:02:32,498 --> 01:02:35,543
<i>and I'm the owner of Ullala Chicken,</i>
<i>the best fried chicken in Jemulpo Market.</i>

973
01:02:36,461 --> 01:02:38,671
<i>I brought the first birthday rings</i>

974
01:02:38,755 --> 01:02:42,258
<i>of my two beloved daughters,</i>
<i>Keum-bo and Jang-mi.</i>

975
01:02:43,718 --> 01:02:45,678
Oh dear, what a voracious eater you are.

976
01:02:45,762 --> 01:02:48,055
Slow down, or you'll get indigestion.

977
01:02:48,639 --> 01:02:49,807
Here.

978
01:02:50,850 --> 01:02:52,852
What is it? Do you know him?

979
01:02:52,935 --> 01:02:53,895
Yes.

980
01:02:53,978 --> 01:02:55,229
No.

981
01:02:55,730 --> 01:02:58,274
He reminds me of the owner
of a fried chicken place I know.

982
01:02:58,357 --> 01:02:59,901
Fried chicken?

983
01:03:01,319 --> 01:03:02,695
- Goodness.
- How cute.

984
01:03:02,779 --> 01:03:04,405
<i>Soon-jung, I love you!</i>

985
01:03:06,240 --> 01:03:07,158
That fool.

986
01:03:07,241 --> 01:03:09,410
How did he even find those rings?

987
01:03:09,494 --> 01:03:10,953
Gosh, he's such a headache.

988
01:03:11,037 --> 01:03:12,663
Oh, my head…

989
01:03:13,247 --> 01:03:14,707
Miss Soon-jung?

990
01:03:24,425 --> 01:03:26,803
<i>Being an executive,</i>
<i>any change in his shareholdings</i>

991
01:03:27,512 --> 01:03:29,222
must be disclosed within five days.

992
01:03:29,305 --> 01:03:30,723
Yes, that's correct.

993
01:03:30,807 --> 01:03:34,435
Failure to comply
becomes grounds for dismissal.

994
01:03:35,019 --> 01:03:38,564
He's obligated to disclose it,
even if he sells just 1%.

995
01:03:38,648 --> 01:03:39,857
Did he not know?

996
01:03:41,192 --> 01:03:43,361
Or did he need it urgently?

997
01:03:43,945 --> 01:03:45,112
Did you say grounds for dismissal?

998
01:03:50,159 --> 01:03:52,495
Do I have any reason
to try to save Oh Deok-gyu?

999
01:03:53,287 --> 01:03:54,247
No.

1000
01:04:02,588 --> 01:04:04,799
Check on all the domestic
slush fund accounts today,

1001
01:04:06,217 --> 01:04:07,468
including the OW's.

1002
01:04:10,054 --> 01:04:11,180
The 5% rule.

1003
01:04:11,264 --> 01:04:14,058
The shareholding disclosure system
has been in effect since 1992,

1004
01:04:14,141 --> 01:04:16,394
when the Securities and Exchange Act
was revised.

1005
01:04:16,477 --> 01:04:19,230
Then it's just a matter of time
before they find out

1006
01:04:19,313 --> 01:04:23,734
that Oh Deok-gyu sold his 9%
and that Yeouido Pirates snatched it up.

1007
01:04:24,318 --> 01:04:25,736
He'll probably try to smooth it over

1008
01:04:25,820 --> 01:04:28,614
through Nam Dong-gi at the FSS
for the time being,

1009
01:04:28,698 --> 01:04:29,782
although it'd only be a temporary fix.

1010
01:04:29,866 --> 01:04:30,783
Does Big Al know this?

1011
01:04:31,617 --> 01:04:32,535
I explained it to him.

1012
01:04:33,911 --> 01:04:36,539
Also, can't you be a little nicer to him?

1013
01:04:36,622 --> 01:04:39,000
Someone needs to stay on guard.

1014
01:04:40,334 --> 01:04:41,335
I must say though,

1015
01:04:41,419 --> 01:04:45,172
he probably won't do us any harm
because of his crush on Hong Jang-mi.

1016
01:04:45,673 --> 01:04:47,008
During our meetings,

1017
01:04:47,091 --> 01:04:49,093
he's either stealing glances
or staring at you.

1018
01:04:50,928 --> 01:04:52,680
Do you have no shame?

1019
01:04:52,763 --> 01:04:54,557
He may have
that free American spirit in him,

1020
01:04:54,640 --> 01:04:56,267
but he's still ten years younger.

1021
01:04:56,350 --> 01:04:58,853
Ten years are enough
to shift rivers and mountains.

1022
01:04:58,936 --> 01:04:59,770
Above all else,

1023
01:04:59,854 --> 01:05:02,690
he's the nephew of Ms. Kang,
who used to live in that small room.

1024
01:05:04,066 --> 01:05:05,902
She's not "Ms. Kang" to me.

1025
01:05:09,947 --> 01:05:11,365
I call Jang-mi

1026
01:05:11,449 --> 01:05:13,659
Ms. Hong now.

1027
01:05:14,827 --> 01:05:17,371
So in Room 301,

1028
01:05:18,039 --> 01:05:20,124
I was actually the youngest,
excluding Bom.

1029
01:05:21,125 --> 01:05:21,959
Right.

1030
01:05:22,043 --> 01:05:25,755
I saw Ms. Hong's father on a TV show
about the gold collection campaign.

1031
01:05:26,631 --> 01:05:28,132
I've met him once.

1032
01:05:34,555 --> 01:05:35,514
And Bom…

1033
01:05:37,224 --> 01:05:39,769
is staying with Ms. Hong's parents.

1034
01:05:46,150 --> 01:05:46,984
Mi-sook.

1035
01:05:56,452 --> 01:05:57,453
Yes?

1036
01:05:57,536 --> 01:05:59,080
<i>Hello? Ms. Hong!</i>

1037
01:05:59,163 --> 01:06:00,748
<i>Mi-sook woke up!</i>

1038
01:06:10,424 --> 01:06:11,842
Mi-sook.

1039
01:06:14,303 --> 01:06:15,221
I'm sorry.

1040
01:06:16,806 --> 01:06:19,517
Eun-joo told me about
everything that's happened.

1041
01:06:20,810 --> 01:06:22,311
I told you.

1042
01:06:22,853 --> 01:06:25,189
Mi-sook and I were close.

1043
01:06:26,232 --> 01:06:27,274
We shared a room.

1044
01:06:34,615 --> 01:06:36,367
Don't worry about Bom.

1045
01:06:36,450 --> 01:06:37,994
She's doing fine.

1046
01:06:38,077 --> 01:06:39,620
She's in Incheon with my parents,

1047
01:06:39,704 --> 01:06:41,539
and I couldn't bring her
because it's too late.

1048
01:06:58,431 --> 01:07:00,182
You can call her big sis.

1049
01:07:00,266 --> 01:07:01,809
Everyone knows she's old.

1050
01:07:07,440 --> 01:07:09,025
Well, <i>we </i>know.

1051
01:07:17,116 --> 01:07:18,200
What?

1052
01:07:18,868 --> 01:07:19,827
Hong Jang-mi?

1053
01:07:19,910 --> 01:07:22,371
The slush fund hidden under her name

1054
01:07:23,330 --> 01:07:24,373
has all been withdrawn.

1055
01:07:25,541 --> 01:07:28,711
Are you saying
she went in person to withdraw it?

1056
01:07:29,253 --> 01:07:30,379
Yes.

1057
01:07:30,463 --> 01:07:33,674
The branch manager said
she had an authorization letter

1058
01:07:34,675 --> 01:07:36,010
and that he even spoke to you.

1059
01:07:39,513 --> 01:07:41,098
Hong Jang-mi…

1060
01:08:37,488 --> 01:08:39,323
{\an8}UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

1061
01:08:39,990 --> 01:08:42,159
{\an8}<i>If we just push out Shin Jung-woo,</i>

1062
01:08:42,243 --> 01:08:44,703
{\an8}we could all maintain peace.

1063
01:08:45,746 --> 01:08:48,499
{\an8}<i>We'll need to reallocate the slush fund.</i>

1064
01:08:48,582 --> 01:08:50,751
{\an8}If the chairman finds out
the OW's slush fund is gone…

1065
01:08:50,835 --> 01:08:53,629
{\an8}We can just retrieve the money
that was stolen.

1066
01:08:53,712 --> 01:08:55,923
{\an8}<i>You guys are secretly planning something,</i>
<i>aren't you?</i>

1067
01:08:56,006 --> 01:08:57,007
{\an8}Oh my god!

1068
01:08:57,091 --> 01:08:58,717
{\an8}<i>What is all that money about?</i>

1069
01:08:59,385 --> 01:09:00,970
{\an8}Hong Keum-bo.

1070
01:09:03,180 --> 01:09:04,098
{\an8}It's a burglar!

1071
01:09:04,807 --> 01:09:06,058
{\an8}<i>We've got a burglar!</i>

1072
01:09:08,185 --> 01:09:13,190
{\an8}Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim

